{{Infobox language |name=Doromu |nativename=Doromu-Koki |states=[[Papua New Guinea]] |region=[[Central Province, Papua New Guinea|Central Province]] |speakers=1,500 |date=2006 |ref=e18 |familycolor=Papuan |fam1=[[Trans–New Guinea languages|Trans–New Guinea]] |fam2=[[Manubaran languages|Manubaran]] |iso3=kqc |glotto=doro1266 |glottorefname=Doromu-Koki |glottofoot = no |dia1=Doromu |dia2=Koki }}
'''Doromu''', or '''Doromu-Koki''', is a [[Manubaran languages|Manubaran language]] spoken in the "[[Bird's Tail]]" of [[Papua New Guinea]]. It has three [[Language variety|varieties]]: Koki, Kokila and Koriko.<ref name>{{Glottolog|doro1266|Doromu-Koki}}</ref>
== Phonology == {{IPA notice}} Doromu has 17 [[phoneme|phonemes]]: 12 are [[consonant|consonants]] and 5 are [[vowel|vowels]].
