'''John Thomas Blake''' (4 April 1853&ndash;26 November 1940) was a New Zealand  surveyor, interpreter, land agent, historian, racehorse owner and trainer. Of [[Māori people|Māori]] descent, he identified with the [[Taranaki Region|Taranaki]] [[iwi]]. He was born in [[Auckland]], [[Auckland]], [[New Zealand]] on 4 April 1853.<ref name="DNZB Blake">{{DNZB|title=John Thomas Blake|first= Patrick|last= Parsons|id=3b38|accessdate=23 April 2017}}</ref>

