{{Infobox writer | name = Rasoul Yunan | image = | caption = | birth_date = 1969 | birth_place = [[Urmia]], Iran | occupation = [[Persian Literature|Persian Poetry]] (mainly) and [[Azerbaijani literature]] | death_date = | death_place = | nationality= Iranian | movement = | children = | }} '''Rasoul Yunan''' ({{Lang-fa|رسول یونان}}, born 1969 in a village near [[Urmia Lake]], [[West Azerbaijan]]) is an [[Iran]]ian poet of [[Iranian Azerbaijani]] descent. He is primarily a Persian poet but is also a translator and writer of [[Persian literature]] and [[Azerbaijani literature]] both. His genre includes [[playwright]], short story, [[dastan]] and modern poetry.
