{{Infobox language |name=Tai Phake |nativename= |states=[[India]] |region=[[Assam]] |ethnicity=[[Tai Phake people]] |speakers=2,000 |date=2007 |ref=e18 |familycolor=Kradai |fam1=[[Kra–Dai languages|Kra–Dai]] |fam2=[[Tai languages|Tai]] |fam3=[[Southwestern Tai languages|Southwestern]] |fam4=Northwestern |script=[[Burmese script]] |iso3=phk |glotto=phak1238 |glottorefname=Phake }}
The '''Tai Phake language''' is spoken in the Buri Dihing Valley of [[Assam]], [[India]]. The ''{{IPA|maːn˧}}'' corresponds to the modern [[Thai language|Thai]] เมือง, ''mueang'', and [[Shan language|Shan]] ''mong'' which corresponds to 'town'.
==Distribution== {| class="wikitable" |+Tai Phake Villages (Morey 2005:22) !c=01| Tai name !c=02| Translation of Tai name !c=03| [[Assamese language|Assamese]]/[[English language|English]] name !c=04| [[List of districts of Assam|District]] |- |c=01| ma:n3 pha:4 ke:5 taü3 |c=02| Lower Phake village |c=03| Namphakey |c=04| [[Dibrugarh]] |- |c=01| ma:n3 pha:k4 ta:5 |c=02| Other side of the river village |c=03| Tipam Phake |c=04| [[Dibrugarh]] |- |c=01| ma:n3 pha:4 ke:5 nɔ6 |c=02| Upper Phake village |c=03| Borphake |c=04| [[Tinsukia]] |- |c=01| niŋ1 kam4 |c=02| Ning kam [[Naga people|Naga]]s |c=03| Nigam Phake |c=04| [[Tinsukia]] |- |c=01| ma:n3 pha:4 naiŋ2 |c=02| Red sky village |c=03| Faneng |c=04| [[Tinsukia]] |- |c=01| məŋ2 la:ŋ2 |c=02| Country of the Lang Nagas |c=03| Mounglang |c=04| [[Tinsukia]] |- |c=01| məŋ2 mɔ1 |c=02| Mine village |c=03| Man Mau |c=04| [[Tinsukia]] |- |c=01| ma:n3 loŋ6 |c=02| Big village |c=03| Man Long |c=04| [[Tinsukia]] |- |c=01| nauŋ1 lai6 |c=02| Nong Lai Nagas |c=03| Nonglai |c=04| - |}
Buragohain (1998) lists the following Tai Phake villages. *Man Phake Tau (Namphake village, [[Assam]]) *Man Tipam (Tipam Phake village, [[Assam]]) *Man Phake Neu (Bor Phake village, [[Assam]]) *Man Mo (Man Mo village, [[Assam]]) *Man Phaneng (Phaneng village, [[Assam]]) *Man Long (Long village, [[Assam]]) *Man Nonglai (Nonglaui village, [[Assam]]) *Man Monglang (Monglang village, [[Assam]]) *Man Nigam (Nigam village, [[Assam]]) *Man Wagun (Wagun village, [[Arunachal Pradesh]]) *Man Lung Kung (Lung Kung village, [[Arunachal Pradesh]])
